WEBVTT

00:01.897 --> 00:03.998
Jack: <i>Over 68 million Americans</i>

00:04.000 --> 00:06.934
<i>leave the safety of
our borders every year.</i>

00:06.936 --> 00:08.269
<i>If danger strikes,</i>

00:08.271 --> 00:10.738
<i>the FBI's international response team</i>

00:10.740 --> 00:13.174
<i>is called into action.</i>

00:14.343 --> 00:16.577
♪

00:23.920 --> 00:25.653
[Gong crashes]

00:25.655 --> 00:28.289
How did we end up volunteering
on <i> this</i> farm?

00:28.291 --> 00:29.757
We should've just gone backpacking.

00:29.759 --> 00:31.025
We signed up for 3 more weeks.

00:31.027 --> 00:32.393
That's 3 too many.

00:32.395 --> 00:35.229
We've only got another
month before school starts.

00:35.231 --> 00:37.364
I just don't wanna waste any more time.

00:37.366 --> 00:39.200
You weren't like this
before he got here.

00:39.202 --> 00:40.167
Don't do that!

00:40.169 --> 00:42.236
Don't make this about Jeff.

00:42.238 --> 00:43.671
Why not? You did.

00:43.673 --> 00:46.307
You cannot honestly
say that this hellhole

00:46.309 --> 00:47.441
is better than the last one we were on.

00:47.443 --> 00:48.976
Shh! He can hear you.

00:48.978 --> 00:50.411
Who, Benz?

00:50.413 --> 00:52.079
He doesn't know what I'm saying.

00:52.081 --> 00:53.314
That's another problem.

00:53.316 --> 00:54.782
I mean, not a single word of English?

00:54.784 --> 00:56.383
There are only five volunteers here.

00:56.385 --> 00:57.551
I feel bad for him.

00:57.553 --> 00:59.520
He watched me shower last night.

00:59.522 --> 01:01.088
Ugh. You give him a good show?

01:01.090 --> 01:02.690
I'm serious. It isn't funny.

01:02.692 --> 01:04.058
If you were so freaked out about it,

01:04.060 --> 01:05.259
why didn't you tell me?

01:05.260 --> 01:06.827
You talking about perv the farmer?

01:06.829 --> 01:09.330
Really? You told <i> him?</i>

01:09.332 --> 01:10.965
I vote that we get outta here.

01:10.967 --> 01:12.366
Bangkok's only an hour drive away.

01:12.368 --> 01:15.169
We can hitch it, we'll
walk it. Won't be that bad.

01:15.171 --> 01:16.604
I told my mom we were staying here

01:16.606 --> 01:18.239
and I don't wanna freak
her out by leaving early.

01:18.241 --> 01:20.574
I already emailed my parents about it.

01:20.576 --> 01:23.544
They wired me money
this morning, $1,500,

01:23.546 --> 01:25.446
at a Western union in Bangkok.

01:25.448 --> 01:26.914
We'll still be in
Thailand the whole time,

01:26.916 --> 01:29.250
but we won't have to stay here. Okay?

01:29.252 --> 01:31.285
Phayu...  [Continues in Thai]

01:36.592 --> 01:39.026
<i>Phayu</i> means “storm”.

01:39.028 --> 01:40.694
Remember, it's typhoon season?

01:40.696 --> 01:41.929
What if one's coming?

01:41.931 --> 01:44.365
It is. And places like this get flooded.

01:44.367 --> 01:47.568
It's a couple days away, but,
I'm not gonna stick around.

01:47.570 --> 01:49.536
You shouldn't, either.

01:49.538 --> 01:51.872
Sold.

01:51.874 --> 01:53.207
She hates me.

01:53.209 --> 01:54.775
No.

01:54.777 --> 01:56.110
Maybe a little.

01:56.112 --> 01:57.678
Don't worry.

01:57.680 --> 01:59.046
[Laughs]

02:01.751 --> 02:03.384
Don't be mad.

02:03.386 --> 02:04.685
I know that it was just gonna be us,

02:04.687 --> 02:06.987
but it's still gonna be fun.
That's not the point.

02:06.989 --> 02:08.622
Okay. Then?

02:08.624 --> 02:10.324
How do you know he's
taking us to Bangkok?

02:10.326 --> 02:12.626
He's lived all over
Thailand for a year already.

02:12.628 --> 02:13.994
He knows where he's going.

02:13.996 --> 02:16.430
Girls get snatched
overseas because they're

02:16.432 --> 02:17.798
stupid enough to follow some guy.

02:17.800 --> 02:21.335
Or stay on some farm with a peeping tom?

02:21.337 --> 02:23.904
Sorry, but I like our chances out here.

02:25.775 --> 02:27.875
[Sinister music plays]

02:27.877 --> 02:29.843
Jeff? [Laughs]

02:29.845 --> 02:31.478
Wh-where are you?

02:32.949 --> 02:34.949
Where'd you go?

02:34.951 --> 02:36.350
Told you he's a jerk.

02:36.352 --> 02:38.018
Jeff, come on. This isn't cool.

02:38.020 --> 02:40.955
He's just being an ass. Right?

02:40.957 --> 02:42.456
[Sinister music continues]

02:42.458 --> 02:44.224
This isn't funny! Jeff!

02:44.226 --> 02:46.527
FBI! Drop your weapon!

02:46.529 --> 02:48.495
Last warning! Drop it now!

02:48.497 --> 02:50.764
[Suspenseful music plays]

02:56.172 --> 02:58.172
You shouldn't have done that.

02:58.174 --> 02:59.406
How about “you're welcome”?

02:59.408 --> 03:00.374
Guy raised his gun.

03:00.376 --> 03:01.842
We could've talked him down.

03:01.844 --> 03:03.377
Jack, last time I checked,

03:03.379 --> 03:05.145
words don't make you bulletproof.

03:05.147 --> 03:07.181
It was a clean shot.
You wanna review it?

03:07.183 --> 03:08.382
Yeah.

03:08.384 --> 03:09.783
Let's forget reviewing it.

03:09.785 --> 03:11.118
How about we go for coffee?

03:11.120 --> 03:12.553
Sure.

03:12.555 --> 03:14.722
[Alert beeps, rings]

03:14.724 --> 03:18.158
Oh, let me guess. Rain check?

03:18.160 --> 03:19.493
Where you headed?

03:19.495 --> 03:20.627
Thailand.

03:20.629 --> 03:22.830
Most exotic place I've
seen lately is Cleveland.

03:22.832 --> 03:24.231
Have some pad Thai for me.

03:24.233 --> 03:26.633
Well, you're welcome to
join us overseas anytime.

03:26.635 --> 03:27.935
We'd love to have you.

03:27.937 --> 03:29.837
Thanks, but I prefer
the comforts of home.

03:29.839 --> 03:31.905
Though, I wouldn't mind
swapping jets with you,

03:31.907 --> 03:33.173
every once in a while.

03:33.175 --> 03:35.642
[Laughs] Not a chance.

03:35.644 --> 03:37.011
[Whistle blows] Double-time it.

03:37.013 --> 03:38.379
Come on, boys. Come on.

03:42.418 --> 03:44.785
♪

03:46.000 --> 03:52.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:54.764 --> 03:57.264
[Laughs]

03:57.266 --> 03:58.532
What took you so long?

03:58.534 --> 04:00.634
Says the girl who had
a huge head start. Huh?

04:00.636 --> 04:03.270
I think that's a new
record for both of us.

04:03.272 --> 04:06.006
[Alert beeps]

04:06.008 --> 04:07.741
It's Jack. I think we got a case.

04:07.743 --> 04:09.043
Yeah, Thailand.

04:09.045 --> 04:10.444
What, are you telepathic now?

04:10.446 --> 04:11.845
Heart rate, phone calls, and texts.

04:11.847 --> 04:13.113
You should really keep up.

04:13.115 --> 04:14.415
Monty's really rubbing off on you.

04:14.417 --> 04:17.684
Hey, just living in 2015.

04:17.685 --> 04:18.851
Oh, look at that.

04:18.853 --> 04:21.387
Finally updated your little flip phone.

04:21.390 --> 04:24.391
It's highly functional.

04:24.393 --> 04:26.160
Race you back.

04:26.162 --> 04:27.461
Ladies first.

04:34.804 --> 04:36.937
[Suspenseful music plays]

04:43.646 --> 04:46.447
♪

04:46.449 --> 04:47.448
Beat ya.

04:47.450 --> 04:48.849
No head start, this time.

04:48.851 --> 04:50.350
Yeah.

04:50.352 --> 04:51.819
Dang!

04:51.821 --> 04:53.287
Does that thing have its own zip code?

04:53.289 --> 04:56.056
Listen, you're not lugging
around car seats and strollers.

04:56.058 --> 04:58.192
Well, wait till they
start playing sports.

04:58.194 --> 04:59.793
You'll have a whole basketball team

04:59.795 --> 05:02.029
squeezed in there.

05:02.031 --> 05:05.199
With murders and accidental
deaths at a record high,

05:05.201 --> 05:07.000
Thailand is quickly becoming one

05:07.002 --> 05:09.036
of the deadliest
destinations for tourists.

05:09.038 --> 05:10.571
I remember those British backpackers

05:10.573 --> 05:12.506
who were murdered there last summer.

05:12.508 --> 05:15.142
Guess that didn't stop
our victims from visiting.

05:15.144 --> 05:16.610
What do we got, Jack?

05:16.612 --> 05:19.680
American college freshmen Laura Johnson

05:19.682 --> 05:21.782
and Sarah Harris went
off the grid 2 days ago

05:21.784 --> 05:23.016
and the latest messages

05:23.018 --> 05:24.985
indicated they were in
hostile surroundings.

05:24.987 --> 05:26.253
<i>We'll be taking off in 3 minutes.</i>

05:26.255 --> 05:27.554
Good morning, handsome.

05:27.556 --> 05:28.856
<i>Hello, lovely.</i>

05:28.858 --> 05:30.891
We got the basics. Fill us in, Monty.

05:30.893 --> 05:33.894
Okay. Laura and Sarah's parents
are on their way in from Ohio.

05:33.896 --> 05:35.229
They confirmed the girls signed up

05:35.231 --> 05:36.763
for a volunteer farming organization

05:36.765 --> 05:38.499
and left the U.S.
right after graduation.

05:38.501 --> 05:40.000
Volunteering on farms is like

05:40.002 --> 05:41.969
the millennials' version of
backpacking across Europe.

05:41.971 --> 05:44.071
<i>These programs have been
around since the 1970s.</i>

05:44.073 --> 05:45.672
Yeah, but they haven't really
caught up with the times.

05:45.674 --> 05:48.041
There's no background checks
for hosts or volunteers.

05:48.043 --> 05:49.476
Not exactly the safest choice.

05:49.478 --> 05:51.011
Their cell phones stopped
transmitting signals

05:51.013 --> 05:52.846
- 48 hours ago.
- What time?

05:52.848 --> 05:54.281
- <i>Midnight.</i>
- Where?

05:54.283 --> 05:56.783
<i>A mile from the farm,
heading north toward Bangkok.</i>

05:56.785 --> 05:58.051
<i>I sent coordinates.</i>

05:58.053 --> 05:59.153
That's the middle of nowhere.

05:59.155 --> 06:00.787
And the girls are adventurous types,

06:00.789 --> 06:02.789
but not adverse-risk takers.

06:02.791 --> 06:04.191
Leaving the farm at midnight

06:04.193 --> 06:05.692
doesn't sound like something they'd do.

06:05.694 --> 06:06.994
Unless they were talked into leaving.

06:06.996 --> 06:08.996
Monty, who's the guy
who met them in Thailand?

06:08.998 --> 06:10.797
Jeff Little.

06:10.799 --> 06:13.066
No cell phone, no credit cards.

06:13.068 --> 06:15.602
According to the girls' photos,
they met at the latest farm.

06:15.604 --> 06:17.271
<i>Laura sent a selfie of her and Jeff,</i>

06:17.273 --> 06:18.672
<i>but Sarah wasn't in the photo</i>

06:18.674 --> 06:20.507
<i>and she didn't say anything
to her mom about it.</i>

06:20.509 --> 06:22.576
Triangle?

06:22.578 --> 06:25.012
Never been a fan of a guy
who comes between friends.

06:25.014 --> 06:26.613
Simmons: Anything we
should be worried about?

06:26.615 --> 06:29.049
Yeah. He was charged with statutory rape

06:29.051 --> 06:30.117
and kicked out of Tulane last year.

06:30.119 --> 06:31.485
<i>He was 19.</i>

06:31.487 --> 06:32.586
Way to bury the lead, Monty.

06:32.588 --> 06:34.054
<i>I'm not sure how serious it was.</i>

06:34.056 --> 06:36.190
<i>The Romeo and Juliet law has
downgraded his conviction</i>

06:36.192 --> 06:37.391
<i>from a felony to a misdemeanor.</i>

06:37.393 --> 06:39.326
<i>He's been livin' all
over Thailand ever since.</i>

06:39.328 --> 06:40.594
With no traceable funds.

06:40.596 --> 06:42.563
Two girls out of their comfort zone,

06:42.565 --> 06:44.431
a guy with no means of income.

06:44.433 --> 06:45.799
And the lure of money.

06:45.801 --> 06:47.167
Laura's mom wired $1,500.

06:47.169 --> 06:48.335
When it wasn't picked up in 2 days,

06:48.337 --> 06:49.403
she called the state department.

06:49.405 --> 06:51.171
Even on foot, from where they were,

06:51.173 --> 06:53.207
it wouldn't take 'em 2
days to walk to Bangkok.

06:53.209 --> 06:55.008
Something bad happened along the way.

06:55.010 --> 06:56.510
What do the Royal Thai Police say?

06:56.512 --> 06:59.079
Without a body, there is no crime.

06:59.081 --> 07:01.381
The director personally
tasked us to investigate

07:01.383 --> 07:02.683
and we're not gonna wait for a body.

07:02.685 --> 07:04.151
- <i>[Chime]</i>
- Good.

07:04.153 --> 07:06.253
Local police should know that
we're all on the same side.

07:06.255 --> 07:09.223
It's not their job to worry
about missing Americans.

07:09.225 --> 07:10.857
It's ours.

07:10.859 --> 07:12.693
[Suspenseful music climbs]

07:19.001 --> 07:21.935
I'm so sorry. This is all my fault.

07:21.937 --> 07:23.237
You got to stop saying that.

07:23.239 --> 07:24.338
But it is.

07:24.340 --> 07:26.506
Benz never watched me shower.

07:26.508 --> 07:27.808
Jeff told me to tell you that.

07:27.810 --> 07:29.142
He knew it was the only thing

07:29.144 --> 07:32.379
that would make you leave.

07:32.381 --> 07:33.747
So do you think Jeff and Benz

07:33.749 --> 07:35.082
are working on this together?

07:35.084 --> 07:37.584
Probably. I don't know.

07:37.586 --> 07:39.052
Hey.

07:39.054 --> 07:40.387
Have you eaten yet?

07:40.389 --> 07:41.455
It's been 2 days.

07:41.457 --> 07:42.522
I can't.

07:42.524 --> 07:44.825
We need our strength to get out of here.

07:44.827 --> 07:46.093
I don't get it.

07:46.095 --> 07:48.262
Why is he feeding us, if
he's just gonna kill us?

07:48.264 --> 07:49.763
Maybe he won't.

07:49.765 --> 07:51.164
Then what is he gonna do?

07:51.166 --> 07:53.300
- [Creak]
- [Eerie music plays]

07:57.473 --> 07:58.538
Ah, get off of me.

07:58.540 --> 07:59.673
Laura? What are you doing?

07:59.675 --> 08:01.341
Ahh! Aah! What is he doing?!

08:01.343 --> 08:02.643
What are you doing to her?!

08:02.645 --> 08:05.545
Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaah!

08:06.131 --> 08:10.377
- Synced and corrected by MasterCookie -
- www.addic7ed.com -

08:27.308 --> 08:30.444
<i>Jack: A Thai proverb reminds us</i>

08:30.446 --> 08:33.614
<i>“what's done in the dark
soon comes to light.”</i>

08:36.751 --> 08:40.254
♪

08:44.560 --> 08:47.094
[Sustained beep]

08:53.427 --> 08:56.561
Clara, glad you're
still taking my calls.

08:56.563 --> 08:58.697
Oh. It's been a while.

08:58.699 --> 09:00.332
So let me guess, you
have not learned Thai

09:00.334 --> 09:02.701
in all your spare time and
you want me to translate.

09:02.703 --> 09:04.870
If all I needed was a translator,

09:04.872 --> 09:06.605
I could Google it.

09:06.607 --> 09:08.373
You've always been way more than that.

09:08.375 --> 09:09.875
Hey, Clara. How you been?

09:09.877 --> 09:12.611
- Good. Yeah, how's Christy?
- Oh, she's amazing.

09:12.613 --> 09:14.880
- How many kids, now?
- Four.

09:14.882 --> 09:16.014
- That's crazy.
- And you?

09:16.016 --> 09:18.283
- How many new languages?
- <i>Zintatu.</i>

09:18.285 --> 09:21.586
- Three, wow. Countries?
- I've lost count.

09:21.588 --> 09:23.922
- My turn. My turn.
- Hi, Mae.

09:23.924 --> 09:25.223
Oh, Mae.

09:25.225 --> 09:27.993
I don't think I've
seen you out of scrubs.

09:27.995 --> 09:29.127
How do you like life in the sunshine?

09:29.129 --> 09:30.529
Well, it beats the freezer.

09:30.531 --> 09:32.531
It turns out, staring at dead bodies

09:32.533 --> 09:35.000
kind of took its toll.
So what are the chances

09:35.002 --> 09:36.268
you're in Thailand right now?

09:36.270 --> 09:38.303
Well, after a few months in Africa,

09:38.305 --> 09:40.071
I decided to roam southeast Asia.

09:40.073 --> 09:42.174
I am studying beliefs about fate.

09:42.176 --> 09:43.308
And?

09:43.310 --> 09:46.678
Everything happens for a reason.

09:46.680 --> 09:48.413
You want the good news or the bad?

09:48.415 --> 09:49.948
- Good.
- Royal Thai police

09:49.950 --> 09:51.683
are setting us up with their office.

09:51.685 --> 09:53.818
For bad, there's a
typhoon off the coast.

09:53.820 --> 09:56.188
Yeah, they're evacuating
low-lying provinces.

09:56.190 --> 09:57.889
The farm could be
underwater in 36 hours,

09:57.891 --> 10:00.358
so I wanna get there before
any evidence is washed away.

10:00.360 --> 10:02.194
- Let's head to the station.
- All right.

10:02.196 --> 10:04.563
Listen, this police
force is a boys' club,

10:04.565 --> 10:05.897
so don't take it personally.

10:05.899 --> 10:07.399
I know they won't shake our hands.

10:07.401 --> 10:09.434
Well, that's a cultural norm
between men and women here.

10:09.436 --> 10:11.703
I'm talking about
professional courtesies.

10:11.705 --> 10:13.905
We're not the two ladies
who will change their minds?

10:13.907 --> 10:15.273
- After 100 years?
- Hmm.

10:15.275 --> 10:16.441
Girl can dream.

10:16.459 --> 10:17.792
Hey, listen. A friend dropped me off.

10:17.794 --> 10:19.160
Can I get a ride?

10:19.162 --> 10:20.828
You know any shortcuts?

10:20.830 --> 10:22.163
A few.

10:23.333 --> 10:25.533
When are you gonna let me drive?

10:25.535 --> 10:26.467
Not today.

10:26.469 --> 10:28.770
♪

10:36.079 --> 10:37.745
So, Laura and Sarah.

10:37.747 --> 10:40.581
They went off the radar for 2.5 days

10:40.583 --> 10:42.583
with a guy they just met, Jeff little.

10:42.585 --> 10:45.553
It doesn't look like he's
made the best life choices

10:45.555 --> 10:46.788
and it doesn't bode well

10:46.790 --> 10:48.222
that he's attached
himself to these girls.

10:48.224 --> 10:52.093
He played favorites,
leaving Sarah odd man out.

10:52.095 --> 10:53.694
You think he split them up for a reason.

10:53.696 --> 10:55.930
I'm thinking he may
have been grooming Laura

10:55.932 --> 10:57.265
as an easy target.

10:57.267 --> 10:58.666
Trafficking. Of course.

10:58.668 --> 10:59.934
He could be a spotter.

10:59.936 --> 11:02.070
I mean, the girls would
trust another American,

11:02.072 --> 11:03.471
when they're on their
own for the first time.

11:03.473 --> 11:05.406
Larger rings are usually centered

11:05.408 --> 11:06.841
in the cities, like Bangkok,

11:06.843 --> 11:08.810
and we know they were
on their way there.

11:08.812 --> 11:10.812
Young, healthy, American?

11:10.814 --> 11:12.513
They'd get top dollar.

11:12.515 --> 11:14.415
Why do humans always find new ways

11:14.417 --> 11:16.517
of hurting one another?

11:16.519 --> 11:18.519
I was just like these girls.

11:18.521 --> 11:20.521
I didn't know you volunteered on a farm.

11:20.523 --> 11:23.124
Yeah. Six in total, all over the U.S.,

11:23.126 --> 11:24.358
when I was 18.

11:24.360 --> 11:25.693
It was a different time back then.

11:25.695 --> 11:28.930
Yeah, but it's the same war, even today.

11:28.932 --> 11:31.165
You want your kids to
have that independence,

11:31.167 --> 11:32.867
but it's so hard to let 'em go.

11:32.869 --> 11:34.769
Yeah. I think my parents knew

11:34.771 --> 11:37.038
I needed to see the world, you know?

11:40.276 --> 11:41.442
Do you miss it?

11:41.444 --> 11:43.044
What, jet lag?

11:43.046 --> 11:44.112
Takeout?

11:44.114 --> 11:45.446
Dead plants at home?

11:45.448 --> 11:46.848
No, my driving.

11:46.850 --> 11:50.451
[Laughs]

11:50.453 --> 11:53.654
I haven't done that for a while.

11:53.656 --> 11:55.423
So, apart from your excellent driving,

11:55.425 --> 11:57.558
do I miss what, exactly?

11:57.560 --> 11:59.127
Saving lives.

12:01.531 --> 12:04.565
Yeah. Yeah, of course.

12:04.567 --> 12:06.467
Yeah, we were pretty good at that.

12:10.673 --> 12:13.574
- [Eerie music plays]
- [Insects buzz]

12:13.576 --> 12:16.110
What's that smell?

12:16.112 --> 12:17.145
Laura?

12:17.147 --> 12:18.179
Yeah.

12:18.181 --> 12:19.947
Do you think this is how it'll end?

12:19.949 --> 12:22.483
- [Door creaks open]
- [Gasp]

12:22.485 --> 12:25.353
Wait. Please, wait.

12:25.355 --> 12:26.921
Laura.

12:26.923 --> 12:28.156
Where... ?

12:28.158 --> 12:30.158
[Gasping]

12:30.160 --> 12:31.325
Where are you taking us?

12:31.327 --> 12:33.728
What are you doing? Just let us go.

12:33.730 --> 12:35.596
We won't tell anyone. Please!

12:35.598 --> 12:36.898
Ahh!

12:43.540 --> 12:46.774
♪

12:51.748 --> 12:54.215
[Speaking local language]

13:00.557 --> 13:03.724
♪

13:09.666 --> 13:11.432
They're not gonna welcome us.

13:11.434 --> 13:12.833
Well, as far as they're concerned,

13:12.835 --> 13:14.502
Laura and Sarah aren't in danger

13:14.504 --> 13:16.504
and, if they are, it's their own doing.

13:16.506 --> 13:18.039
Here we go.

13:30.954 --> 13:32.153
Buhni Taksin. Welcome.

13:32.155 --> 13:34.322
Jack Garrett. Good to meet you.

13:34.324 --> 13:38.793
This is my team, Agent Simmons, Jarvis.

13:38.795 --> 13:41.095
Cultural expert Clara Seger

13:41.097 --> 13:42.563
will be consulting with us.

13:42.565 --> 13:43.864
We'd like the map of the
province, so we can check

13:43.866 --> 13:45.600
the routes they may have taken

13:45.602 --> 13:48.836
- in and out of the farm.
- [Speaking thai]

13:48.838 --> 13:50.438
I don't speak Thai.

13:50.440 --> 13:53.975
She does.

13:53.977 --> 13:56.911
Of course. One moment.

13:56.913 --> 14:00.848
The royal Thai police
force is 250,000 strong,

14:00.850 --> 14:03.084
but only 70 officers are female

14:03.086 --> 14:06.087
and they were only sworn in 2 years ago.

14:06.089 --> 14:07.588
Against the law to smile?

14:10.326 --> 14:11.659
- Here you go.
- Oh, thanks.

14:11.661 --> 14:13.327
We need a search team at the farm.

14:13.329 --> 14:15.029
How many officers are joining us?

14:15.031 --> 14:16.464
I'm the only one assigned to you.

14:16.466 --> 14:20.034
Others are prepping for the
storm evacuation protocols.

14:20.036 --> 14:22.637
Okay, well, we need to get
out to the farm right away.

14:22.639 --> 14:24.005
We need to talk to the owner.

14:24.007 --> 14:25.539
He's waiting for us.

14:29.712 --> 14:31.045
<i>We are now receiving footage</i>

14:31.047 --> 14:33.648
<i>of the typhoon making
landfall in Cambodia.</i>

14:33.650 --> 14:35.683
<i>It's moved north and is due
to hit Thailand in 24 hours.</i>

14:35.685 --> 14:39.053
- Oh. Oh, it's you.
- Mary. Frank.

14:39.055 --> 14:41.055
Oh, I can't believe this is happening.

14:41.057 --> 14:43.190
- Tell me they're okay.
- My team is there now.

14:43.192 --> 14:45.026
We're trying to put
some pieces together.

14:45.028 --> 14:46.527
Please.

14:46.529 --> 14:47.828
We should never have let them go

14:47.830 --> 14:49.196
to Thailand on their own.

14:49.198 --> 14:51.832
Laura sent some pictures
of a guy named Jeff little,

14:51.834 --> 14:54.268
said he was volunteering
at different farms, too.

14:54.270 --> 14:56.203
It seems like they were friends.
Have you reached out to him?

14:56.205 --> 14:57.972
I read about Jeff online.

14:57.974 --> 14:59.540
He raped a girl in college.

14:59.542 --> 15:01.409
- He did what?
- Oh, my god.

15:01.411 --> 15:05.513
Our girls weren't in
trouble, until they met him.

15:05.515 --> 15:08.249
Are those his parents?

15:08.251 --> 15:09.550
Excuse me.

15:11.521 --> 15:13.888
Mr. and Mrs. little, come with me.

15:15.425 --> 15:18.359
[Suspenseful music plays]

15:24.033 --> 15:25.266
We toured the main property.

15:25.268 --> 15:27.168
- Taksin: Already?
- We got here 10 minutes ago.

15:28.671 --> 15:31.205
I should get a motorbike like that.

15:31.207 --> 15:32.506
Have you met Benz yet?

15:32.508 --> 15:33.874
Yeah. He let us look around.

15:33.876 --> 15:35.676
None of his doors have locks.

15:35.678 --> 15:37.678
Laura and Sarah stayed
in a crowded bunkroom

15:37.680 --> 15:38.879
with two other girls from England,

15:38.881 --> 15:40.381
who said that they packed
up their stuff and left.

15:40.383 --> 15:41.849
Guys' room is even worse.

15:41.851 --> 15:43.084
Besides this road in here,

15:43.086 --> 15:44.418
there's only two other
paths that lead out.

15:44.420 --> 15:46.420
So we should be looking
for footprints, tire tracks,

15:46.422 --> 15:47.888
anything that helps us
figure out what went wrong

15:47.890 --> 15:50.024
- and where.
- Simmons, you two get started.

15:50.026 --> 15:51.125
- Got it.
- I will join you.

15:51.127 --> 15:52.493
All right. Let's do it.

15:52.495 --> 15:54.829
Now, part of my job is to
trace any digital footprint,

15:54.831 --> 15:56.997
but I can't find anything on Jeff.

15:56.999 --> 15:58.432
When was the last
time you talked to him?

15:58.434 --> 15:59.533
Almost 3 months ago.

15:59.535 --> 16:01.102
He was volunteering at farms

16:01.104 --> 16:02.770
through a few different programs.

16:02.772 --> 16:04.572
At least I knew he was getting food

16:04.574 --> 16:05.973
and a safe place to sleep.

16:05.975 --> 16:07.274
Have you sent him any money?

16:07.276 --> 16:08.509
He wouldn't accept it, if we did.

16:08.511 --> 16:09.910
That whole thing at Tulane?

16:09.912 --> 16:12.480
Drove a wedge between us, as a family.

16:12.482 --> 16:14.749
He didn't feel supported, so he left.

16:14.751 --> 16:16.951
I gave him my credit card,
though, for emergencies.

16:16.953 --> 16:18.486
But he's never used it.

16:21.818 --> 16:23.352
____

16:23.739 --> 16:25.581
____

16:25.711 --> 16:27.287
____

16:27.964 --> 16:31.699
[Speaking Thai]

16:33.499 --> 16:35.074
____

16:35.601 --> 16:36.790
____

16:36.952 --> 16:37.964
____

16:38.123 --> 16:40.838
____

16:41.013 --> 16:43.189
____

16:43.934 --> 16:46.860
____

16:46.916 --> 16:48.115
He's overwhelmed.

16:48.117 --> 16:50.017
His wife, she's sick.

16:50.019 --> 16:52.186
Ask him if there was
anything out of the ordinary

16:52.188 --> 16:53.954
with the girls. Were they arguing?

16:53.956 --> 16:56.457
[Conversing in Thai]

17:07.002 --> 17:09.603
He says the boy spent more
time with Laura than Sarah,

17:09.605 --> 17:12.807
so Sarah seemed lonely and Sarah tried

17:12.809 --> 17:16.609
to speak in Thai, which
Benz says was thoughtful.

17:16.612 --> 17:19.814
Tell him I appreciate the information.

17:19.816 --> 17:21.415
[Speaking Thai]

17:21.416 --> 17:22.883
[Speaking Thai]

17:26.422 --> 17:27.721
What do you think?

17:27.723 --> 17:29.723
Well, he's exhausted,
but willing to talk.

17:29.725 --> 17:32.426
He seems embarrassed of the
conditions he provides here,

17:32.428 --> 17:33.828
and he's not surprised that they left.

17:33.830 --> 17:35.396
They're not the first kids to go.

17:35.398 --> 17:36.697
And I spotted a Buddha,

17:36.699 --> 17:39.033
which means he believes in karma.

17:39.035 --> 17:40.334
What do you think?

17:40.336 --> 17:43.804
Agreed. He was making
eye contact with you

17:43.806 --> 17:45.606
and didn't seem like
he was acting suspicious

17:45.608 --> 17:46.874
or hiding anything.

17:46.876 --> 17:49.176
Yeah. So, that leaves Jeff.

17:49.178 --> 17:51.278
He's the one thing
that still sticks out.

17:51.280 --> 17:53.113
- [Ring]
- A stranger who forced himself

17:53.115 --> 17:55.316
- between two girls.
- [Ring]

17:55.318 --> 17:57.918
It's Monty.

17:57.920 --> 17:59.153
Russell Montgomery,

17:59.155 --> 18:00.387
<i>as I live and breathe.</i>

18:00.389 --> 18:02.089
Is that you, Clara? How you been?

18:02.091 --> 18:03.123
Better, now.

18:03.125 --> 18:05.125
Let me put you on speaker.

18:05.127 --> 18:06.660
Our challenge here is to find something

18:06.662 --> 18:08.128
before the wind and
the rain wash it away.

18:08.130 --> 18:09.330
Now, I got no tire tracks,

18:09.332 --> 18:14.335
but the footprints
are the freshest here.

18:14.337 --> 18:15.636
And here.

18:15.638 --> 18:18.506
[Ominous music plays]

18:18.508 --> 18:20.107
Looks like the girls split up.

18:24.680 --> 18:26.480
Hold up. We got blood.

18:29.452 --> 18:30.951
Directionality of the spatter says

18:30.953 --> 18:32.987
whoever this belongs
to is headed that way.

18:32.989 --> 18:37.091
[Ring]

18:37.093 --> 18:38.359
Hey, Jack.

18:38.361 --> 18:40.327
Monty just tracked the
littles' credit card

18:40.329 --> 18:42.162
to an Internet cafe in Bangkok.

18:42.164 --> 18:44.532
<i>Okay, well, we got some
blood out here on a path.</i>

18:44.534 --> 18:46.400
You and Mae find the
source of that blood.

18:46.402 --> 18:47.868
<i>Clara and I will head back to the city.</i>

18:47.870 --> 18:49.403
You got it.

18:54.944 --> 18:57.177
♪

19:09.792 --> 19:12.226
<i>[Music plays]</i>

19:12.228 --> 19:13.694
Hi. How are you?

19:23.839 --> 19:25.573
You see what I see?

19:25.575 --> 19:26.907
Yep.

19:30.780 --> 19:33.380
And that is definitely not Jeff.

19:33.382 --> 19:36.016
[Suspenseful music climbs]

19:36.018 --> 19:37.384
Aah!

19:41.991 --> 19:43.524
[Shouting in Thai]

19:50.499 --> 19:54.001
♪

20:00.476 --> 20:02.943
♪

20:02.945 --> 20:05.312
[Speaking Thai]

20:05.314 --> 20:06.714
[Shouting in Thai]

20:06.716 --> 20:08.382
Oh! Ay!

20:11.253 --> 20:13.354
Oh! Ah! Ah!

20:19.362 --> 20:21.228
[Shouting in Thai]

20:21.230 --> 20:22.496
Ay!

20:26.636 --> 20:29.003
[Shouting in Thai]

20:29.005 --> 20:30.237
Huah!

20:34.010 --> 20:35.542
[Speaking Thai]

20:35.544 --> 20:37.978
[Shouting in Thai]

20:37.980 --> 20:39.446
He says he didn't hurt him.

20:39.448 --> 20:41.281
[Speaking thai] Hey!

20:41.283 --> 20:44.151
[Ring]

20:44.153 --> 20:45.919
We've got Jeff's stuff.

20:45.921 --> 20:47.454
We got Jeff.

20:51.994 --> 20:54.561
Jeff's dead.

20:57.910 --> 20:59.873
____

20:59.926 --> 21:01.158
Make sure you guys
build a perimeter and then push outward.

21:01.160 --> 21:02.493
No. Yes, I have to.

21:02.495 --> 21:03.794
If you find anything, call me.

21:03.796 --> 21:04.962
We'll come back and reestablish as well.

21:04.964 --> 21:06.097
- I have to go down and get...
- No.

21:06.099 --> 21:07.331
You are not allowed.

21:07.333 --> 21:10.034
- I can't get clear photos from...
- Hey, hey. Come here.

21:12.705 --> 21:14.538
Listen, now that there's a body,

21:14.540 --> 21:16.641
this is the royal Thai
police's investigation.

21:16.643 --> 21:17.875
If we overstep, we'll be kicked out

21:17.877 --> 21:19.076
before we find Laura and Sarah.

21:19.078 --> 21:20.144
Why not work together?

21:20.146 --> 21:21.679
Because they have a process, a system.

21:21.681 --> 21:24.215
We have to respect it.

21:24.217 --> 21:25.483
You mean to tell me
you can't find anything

21:25.485 --> 21:27.018
in those fancy photos?

21:30.356 --> 21:32.423
Apparent C.O.D. is a severed carotid.

21:32.425 --> 21:33.991
But the elements eroded the flesh,

21:33.993 --> 21:37.028
so I can't tell if
there was any hesitation.

21:37.030 --> 21:39.130
What is this on the back of his neck?

21:39.132 --> 21:40.431
Got a botched tattoo?

21:40.433 --> 21:42.099
I could tell ya, if I
had access to his body,

21:42.101 --> 21:44.468
but, since I don't...

21:44.470 --> 21:47.672
The only way to know is
to examine him myself.

21:49.842 --> 21:52.009
[Eerie music plays]

21:54.213 --> 21:56.514
[Sobbing]

21:59.318 --> 22:00.718
Ah!

22:00.720 --> 22:03.120
[Gasping] Ah!

22:03.122 --> 22:04.388
[Gasp]

22:08.628 --> 22:09.894
Aaaah!

22:09.896 --> 22:11.862
[Growling]

22:11.864 --> 22:12.830
Run.

22:12.832 --> 22:14.498
- What?
- Run.

22:14.500 --> 22:16.100
He's telling us to run.

22:16.102 --> 22:19.670
[Crying out]

22:19.672 --> 22:22.373
[Growling]

22:22.375 --> 22:23.874
<i>Tropical Storm Hunter is moving</i>

22:23.876 --> 22:25.710
<i>up the southern coast of Thailand.</i>

22:25.712 --> 22:28.212
<i>It's due to hit Bangkok and
the surrounding provinces</i>

22:28.214 --> 22:29.447
<i>tomorrow evening.</i>

22:29.449 --> 22:31.916
<i>Many of the farms outside
Bangkok are lowlands</i>

22:31.918 --> 22:33.684
<i>and are in danger of flooding.</i>

22:33.686 --> 22:36.654
Can you excuse us for a moment, please?

22:36.656 --> 22:39.190
[Melancholy tune plays]

22:54.474 --> 22:56.474
I'm so sorry.

23:00.580 --> 23:01.979
[Crying]

23:04.117 --> 23:06.250
[Sobbing]

23:12.725 --> 23:15.226
How do you know Jeff
little wasn't involved?

23:15.228 --> 23:16.894
He had a detailed journal,

23:16.896 --> 23:18.429
telling us he was soul-searching.

23:18.431 --> 23:20.231
There were no indicators
he was suffering

23:20.233 --> 23:21.398
any psychosis.

23:21.400 --> 23:23.434
He was just a lost 20-year-old kid.

23:23.436 --> 23:24.869
I will let the others know.

23:24.871 --> 23:26.337
We're ready for a profile.

23:26.339 --> 23:27.838
Gather your officers.

23:27.840 --> 23:30.908
[Speaking Thai]

23:30.910 --> 23:32.877
Now that Jeff is cleared as a suspect,

23:32.879 --> 23:35.212
we need to focus on what
the unsub did to his body.

23:35.214 --> 23:36.781
I want you to take the lead on this.

23:36.783 --> 23:38.516
- You think he'll listen?
- Well, if there's only

23:38.518 --> 23:40.818
you two talking, he won't have a choice.

23:40.820 --> 23:42.853
Simmons and I are gonna
go talk to the kid,

23:42.855 --> 23:45.289
find out what else he
saw at the crime scene.

23:45.291 --> 23:46.891
Knock 'em out.

23:49.962 --> 23:51.729
[Hyperventilating]

23:57.637 --> 24:01.105
Aaaaah-aah-aah!

24:01.107 --> 24:02.540
[Gasp] Shh, shh!

24:02.542 --> 24:04.141
Aah! Shh!

24:06.145 --> 24:07.144
[Growl]

24:07.146 --> 24:09.046
Our victim's remains tell us a lot

24:09.048 --> 24:10.915
about out unknown subject, or unsub.

24:10.917 --> 24:12.550
Yes, that he liked to use a knife.

24:12.552 --> 24:13.884
It's more than that.

24:13.886 --> 24:16.287
He abducted three people,
but he killed the male first.

24:16.289 --> 24:18.222
And the time of death says
that he did it right away.

24:18.224 --> 24:19.957
- Why would he do that?
- Most likely to get rid

24:19.959 --> 24:22.393
of competition and establish dominance.

24:22.395 --> 24:23.494
Has he killed the girls?

24:23.496 --> 24:25.129
It's doubtful he's done that, yet.

24:25.131 --> 24:26.864
He's a power-assertive offender

24:26.866 --> 24:28.199
who gets off on control.

24:28.201 --> 24:30.634
He'll wanna prolong that experience.

24:30.636 --> 24:31.969
And he's not gonna get rid of them

24:31.971 --> 24:33.537
until his psychological needs are met.

24:33.539 --> 24:35.172
How does any of this help us find him?

24:35.174 --> 24:36.473
Because everything that he does

24:36.475 --> 24:39.243
gives us a clue to what makes him tick.

24:39.245 --> 24:40.878
He killed Jeff little on the trail,

24:40.880 --> 24:42.680
but he carried his
body down to the ravine,

24:42.682 --> 24:45.382
which contaminated
any physical evidence.

24:45.384 --> 24:47.518
He's more criminally
sophisticated than we thought.

24:47.520 --> 24:48.719
He's violent.

24:48.721 --> 24:51.355
And hunting at night
could be a learned behavior

24:51.357 --> 24:52.756
and it also tells us
that he doesn't have

24:52.758 --> 24:55.259
the social skills to pull off a ruse.

24:55.261 --> 24:56.260
You need to search for anyone

24:56.262 --> 24:57.394
recently released from prison.

24:57.396 --> 25:00.231
Ask if anyone fits
this behavioral pattern.

25:00.233 --> 25:01.465
Thank you.

25:07.974 --> 25:10.140
Our morgues are in the hospital,

25:10.142 --> 25:11.408
but, since this is active,

25:11.410 --> 25:13.043
they're going to keep the body close.

25:13.045 --> 25:15.813
I don't know when our
medical examiner can be here.

25:15.815 --> 25:19.717
Okay. Thank you.

25:19.719 --> 25:22.186
The body has been
deteriorating for 2.5 days.

25:22.188 --> 25:23.754
It's gonna get worse without a freezer.

25:23.756 --> 25:25.322
You might wanna take a look.

25:25.324 --> 25:28.259
Just know they're not gonna
answer any of your questions.

25:28.261 --> 25:29.793
I'm not gonna ask any.

25:37.536 --> 25:38.936
Aaah!

25:38.938 --> 25:41.472
[Gasp] Shh! Shh! Shh! Shh!

25:41.474 --> 25:43.807
Ah! Oh!

25:43.809 --> 25:45.542
Okay.

25:45.544 --> 25:47.578
I saw some comfrey
root leaves back there.

25:47.580 --> 25:49.513
They'll help slow the bleeding.

25:49.515 --> 25:50.781
Hurry back.

25:53.853 --> 25:56.887
[Suspenseful music plays]

26:02.995 --> 26:06.230
♪

26:13.005 --> 26:15.339
♪

26:18.811 --> 26:20.311
Clean cut, no hesitation.

26:20.313 --> 26:22.746
Okay, let's get some
of this mud off here.

26:28.587 --> 26:31.055
There it is.

26:31.057 --> 26:32.289
It's not a tattoo.

26:32.291 --> 26:34.191
It's not a birthmark.

26:37.229 --> 26:38.929
Inflamed tissue, but
there's no blood pool,

26:38.931 --> 26:40.698
so this was done postmortem.

26:42.969 --> 26:44.535
[Doorknob rattles]

26:52.178 --> 26:54.979
My name is Kosum.

26:54.981 --> 26:56.513
My name is Mae.

26:59.485 --> 27:01.185
I think you lost this, Mae.

27:03.589 --> 27:05.122
Yes. Thank you.

27:08.928 --> 27:10.461
Is there a problem here?

27:33.886 --> 27:35.919
[Beeping]

27:35.921 --> 27:37.221
<i>Go ahead, Mae.</i>

27:37.223 --> 27:38.622
Hey, did you get the photo?

27:38.624 --> 27:39.590
<i>Uh, yeah.</i>

27:39.592 --> 27:41.825
Looks like a symbol of some kind.

27:41.827 --> 27:43.927
It's not on a flat surface,
so I can't tell, for sure.

27:43.929 --> 27:45.195
Will you fill it out and run it

27:45.197 --> 27:47.197
against the popular
symbols in this area?

27:47.199 --> 27:49.633
<i>Anything religious, cultural, political.</i>

27:49.635 --> 27:51.135
I'm already on it.

27:55.875 --> 27:59.376
[Siren wails]

27:59.378 --> 28:01.011
Here you guys are.

28:01.013 --> 28:02.780
I thought you left me.

28:02.782 --> 28:05.049
Thought about it.

28:05.051 --> 28:06.383
Did you get anything from the local kid?

28:06.385 --> 28:08.085
No. He found the body,
but was too afraid

28:08.087 --> 28:09.720
to talk to the authorities.

28:09.722 --> 28:11.188
What'd you find, Mae?

28:11.190 --> 28:12.723
Zero hesitation on the kill.

28:12.725 --> 28:14.191
Used a heavy blade.

28:14.193 --> 28:17.628
He's definitely
comfortable with a weapon.

28:17.630 --> 28:19.029
The skin is raised, but there's

28:19.031 --> 28:20.964
no blood pool or irritation.

28:20.966 --> 28:22.366
This was done postmortem.

28:22.368 --> 28:24.101
Is that from a branding iron?

28:24.103 --> 28:25.936
Monty's running it now.

28:25.938 --> 28:27.438
That's pretty specific.

28:32.111 --> 28:33.877
Simmons, what's in your head?

28:33.879 --> 28:36.113
Uh, I think the unsub
watched and waited,

28:36.115 --> 28:37.881
most likely from higher ground,

28:37.883 --> 28:39.817
till the three of them were isolated.

28:39.819 --> 28:41.852
He attacked Jeff first,
the biggest threat.

28:41.854 --> 28:44.154
And he had a compulsive
need to brand him,

28:44.156 --> 28:46.390
like his prey.

28:46.392 --> 28:48.225
What if that's why he's
kept the girls alive?

28:49.995 --> 28:51.528
He's hunting them.

28:51.530 --> 28:55.732
[Growling]

28:55.734 --> 28:59.436
Sarah, help! No. Help! No.

28:59.438 --> 29:02.005
Ow. Ow.

29:02.007 --> 29:03.273
Sarah!

29:03.275 --> 29:04.942
[Crying out]

29:06.779 --> 29:09.513
[Gasp]

29:09.515 --> 29:10.914
Ah!

29:10.916 --> 29:12.449
Come on! Let's go!

29:13.853 --> 29:15.986
[Suspenseful music climbs]

29:21.030 --> 29:22.998
Winds and rain are picking
up in certain areas.

29:23.007 --> 29:24.506
We do not have much time.

29:24.508 --> 29:27.076
Those areas are surrounded
by miles of dense jungle.

29:27.078 --> 29:28.344
How do we find them?

29:28.346 --> 29:30.379
We've marked the
abduction and dump sites.

29:30.381 --> 29:32.414
Until we have a third,
it's impossible to know

29:32.416 --> 29:35.184
which direction will lead
to the unsub's comfort zone.

29:35.186 --> 29:36.452
What is that?

29:36.454 --> 29:38.487
It's a narrowed-down
area where he feels safe.

29:38.489 --> 29:40.289
- Most serial killers...
- What?

29:40.291 --> 29:42.057
We do not have a serial killer.

29:42.059 --> 29:43.425
There's only one victim.

29:43.427 --> 29:44.760
He took three people at once.

29:44.762 --> 29:46.328
In its nature, that's serial.

29:46.330 --> 29:48.464
Look, apologies if we've offended you.

29:48.466 --> 29:50.299
Every culture has their version

29:50.301 --> 29:51.567
of multiple violations.

29:51.569 --> 29:53.969
How do you know any of
this after only one murder?

29:53.971 --> 29:55.604
Because he left a calling card.

29:55.606 --> 29:57.973
Yeah, in this case, he branded Jeff.

29:57.975 --> 30:00.109
What brand are you talking about?

30:00.111 --> 30:01.377
[Beep]

30:03.681 --> 30:08.817
Mae was able to lift a
partial image from Jeff's body.

30:08.819 --> 30:11.420
My analyst at home is
trying to identify it.

30:17.061 --> 30:18.560
Hey. I've got it.

30:18.562 --> 30:21.030
I'm sending it to you now.

30:21.032 --> 30:24.533
You're the best, Monty.

30:24.535 --> 30:26.435
Here you go.

30:26.437 --> 30:28.937
I've seen this before.

30:28.939 --> 30:30.205
Mani!

30:30.207 --> 30:32.207
It was on mutilated
animals earlier this year.

30:32.209 --> 30:34.243
Torturing animals is a precursor

30:34.245 --> 30:35.511
to serial killing.

30:35.513 --> 30:37.212
It allows him to perfect his M.O.

30:37.214 --> 30:38.881
And find his ritual.

30:38.883 --> 30:41.483
Where'd you find the
animals? [Speaking thai]

30:43.120 --> 30:44.486
[Gasping]

30:44.488 --> 30:46.422
Ah! Ah!

30:46.424 --> 30:48.557
I can't make it. You should go.

30:48.559 --> 30:50.326
I'm not about to leave you.

30:50.328 --> 30:51.460
Now, get up.

30:51.462 --> 30:54.229
Ow!

30:54.231 --> 30:56.165
Got the three points, the
hunting and the kill zones

30:56.167 --> 30:58.100
and, now, where the
dead animals were found.

31:05.976 --> 31:07.409
What's Chonburi province known for?

31:07.411 --> 31:08.944
Wild-boar hunting.

31:08.946 --> 31:11.513
And land disputes, going
back many generations.

31:11.515 --> 31:13.982
We're looking for a
family who's lost the most.

31:13.984 --> 31:15.317
- I know a few.
- [Thunder rumbles]

31:15.319 --> 31:16.719
Simmons, get Monty on the phone.

31:16.721 --> 31:18.954
He can help us narrow it down.

31:18.956 --> 31:20.255
According to Thai records,

31:20.257 --> 31:22.091
the only survivor is 20-year-old klahan.

31:22.093 --> 31:23.659
Clara: That means “very brave”.

31:23.661 --> 31:26.328
My guess is he had to prove it,
through a lifetime of violence.

31:26.330 --> 31:28.731
Yeah, just spent a year
in Samut Prakarn prison

31:28.733 --> 31:30.733
for attacking trespassers with a spear.

31:30.735 --> 31:33.268
He was released and, days
later, his grandmother died.

31:33.270 --> 31:34.903
She was the last remaining relative.

31:34.905 --> 31:38.173
That stressor, combined with
his homicidal tendencies,

31:38.175 --> 31:39.842
created the perfect storm.

31:39.844 --> 31:41.543
Are there any cultural traditions

31:41.545 --> 31:44.380
for the last remaining
member of a family?

31:44.382 --> 31:46.548
This could be Ullambana.

31:46.550 --> 31:47.850
Come again?

31:47.852 --> 31:49.852
It's a Mahayana festival.

31:49.854 --> 31:52.521
When followers believed
the gates of hell open

31:52.523 --> 31:55.090
and ghosts of ancestors
visit the living,

31:55.092 --> 31:57.993
traditionally, offerings
are made to the departed.

31:57.995 --> 32:00.629
The unsub, sacrificing
humans to his dead family.

32:00.631 --> 32:03.599
And he's proven they're worthy
by hunting them for 3 days.

32:03.601 --> 32:05.701
He'll kill them before the storm hits.

32:05.703 --> 32:08.537
[Thunder rumbles]

32:08.539 --> 32:11.540
[Suspenseful music plays]

32:11.542 --> 32:13.075
[Gasping]

32:13.077 --> 32:14.676
There's something up ahead.

32:23.087 --> 32:24.720
Hello!

32:24.722 --> 32:25.988
Hello!

32:30.361 --> 32:33.195
[Eerie music plays]

32:36.567 --> 32:38.100
Oh, God.

32:38.102 --> 32:40.002
What's that smell?

32:40.004 --> 32:41.637
We're back where we started.

32:41.639 --> 32:44.506
- [Shuddering]
- [ Suspenseful music climbs]

32:51.140 --> 32:52.439
- [Growling]
- [Gasp]

32:54.643 --> 32:56.009
[Growling]

32:56.011 --> 32:57.478
Run!

32:59.782 --> 33:01.782
Ru-u-u-u-u-n.

33:01.784 --> 33:04.852
[Suspenseful music plays]

33:11.627 --> 33:14.862
♪

33:21.637 --> 33:24.872
♪

33:31.647 --> 33:33.313
♪

33:33.315 --> 33:36.517
Huh. These can be used
for self-mutilation.

33:36.519 --> 33:38.085
Maybe that's his way
of expressing emotion.

33:38.087 --> 33:39.419
And, in this culture, it's a way

33:39.421 --> 33:41.622
of sacrificing yourself
to a higher power.

33:41.624 --> 33:43.490
Here's the branding iron.

33:43.492 --> 33:45.826
Oh, check this out, guys.

33:45.828 --> 33:48.128
“Tell our parents we're sorry”.

33:50.199 --> 33:51.899
Looks like he's using the
topography as his trap.

33:51.901 --> 33:53.233
Look at these terrain features.

33:53.235 --> 33:55.128
There's a river to one
side, mountains on another,

33:55.548 --> 33:57.314
- and a cliff.
- Means they're in this area.

33:57.316 --> 33:59.016
Yeah, but it could
take hours to find them.

33:59.018 --> 34:00.250
Let's move out.

34:00.252 --> 34:01.852
Wait. We go out there like

34:01.854 --> 34:04.421
a bunch of alpha males, he'll attack.

34:04.423 --> 34:05.789
You wanna talk him down?

34:05.791 --> 34:07.858
Or you want Taksin to do it?

34:07.860 --> 34:09.560
I want you to.

34:09.562 --> 34:10.860
He's not gonna listen to me.

34:10.862 --> 34:13.163
There were many important
women in his life.

34:13.165 --> 34:14.864
He'll listen.

34:14.867 --> 34:16.367
He had a close family

34:16.369 --> 34:17.501
and they were important to him.

34:17.503 --> 34:18.768
Just build a rapport

34:18.771 --> 34:21.871
and he'll respect what you have to say.

34:21.873 --> 34:23.873
This doesn't have to be his fate.

34:23.876 --> 34:25.342
That's right.

34:26.545 --> 34:28.978
- [Panting]
- [Moaning]

34:28.981 --> 34:31.514
[Ominous music plays]

34:35.286 --> 34:38.355
[Eerie music plays]

34:41.560 --> 34:43.893
- Oof!
- [Growling]

34:43.896 --> 34:45.829
Sarah, look out! He's coming!

34:47.533 --> 34:48.799
Uh!

34:54.206 --> 34:56.806
[Growling]

34:56.809 --> 34:59.743
Please, let us go.

34:59.745 --> 35:02.446
[Speaking Thai]

35:02.448 --> 35:03.781
Simmons, cover her.

35:03.783 --> 35:05.082
Hey, hey. Hey, hey.

35:05.084 --> 35:06.316
[Grunting]

35:06.318 --> 35:07.551
Okay.

35:10.756 --> 35:11.822
[Shouts]

35:11.824 --> 35:13.023
Okay. Okay.

35:13.025 --> 35:14.925
[Speaking Thai]

35:14.927 --> 35:16.827
Agh!

35:55.868 --> 35:57.668
♪

35:57.670 --> 35:59.169
Yeah.

35:59.171 --> 36:00.437
Oh!

36:22.628 --> 36:25.162
[Shouting in Thai]

36:32.171 --> 36:35.405
♪

36:38.744 --> 36:41.144
He was all alone.

36:47.520 --> 36:49.786
♪

36:54.660 --> 36:57.895
♪

37:08.407 --> 37:11.375
[Melancholy tune plays]

37:18.150 --> 37:21.385
♪

37:28.160 --> 37:31.395
♪

37:38.170 --> 37:41.405
♪

37:48.180 --> 37:51.415
♪

37:55.588 --> 37:57.854
So I just set the record
for fastest paperwork.

37:57.856 --> 37:59.489
Yeah. Still took you all day.

37:59.491 --> 38:01.024
Let me see that.

38:02.628 --> 38:04.861
Royal Thai police coin. Very nice.

38:04.863 --> 38:06.330
Yeah, Monty's gonna love it.

38:06.332 --> 38:07.898
Oh, yeah.

38:07.900 --> 38:09.199
By the way, I don't mean to brag,

38:09.201 --> 38:10.634
but did you see that back there?

38:10.636 --> 38:11.635
What?

38:11.637 --> 38:14.137
Taksin had a hint of a smile.

38:14.139 --> 38:15.505
Yeah? Doesn't surprise me.

38:15.507 --> 38:17.140
You are determined, stubborn,

38:17.142 --> 38:18.442
likely to win someone over.

38:18.444 --> 38:20.877
In this job, that's a good combo.

38:20.879 --> 38:23.080
Does that mean I get to drive the bike?

38:23.082 --> 38:25.749
No.

38:25.751 --> 38:28.185
Did you hear they downgraded the storm?

38:28.187 --> 38:31.488
Yeah? Somebody should
tell that to the rain.

38:31.490 --> 38:33.023
[Thunder rumbles]

38:36.295 --> 38:39.896
♪

38:44.036 --> 38:45.302
[Melancholy tune plays]

38:45.304 --> 38:47.337
These winds aren't bad.

38:47.339 --> 38:49.873
Should make the flight home better.

38:52.611 --> 38:55.946
I've been out of the
game too long, Jack.

38:55.948 --> 38:57.914
I'm sitting here,
feeling sorry for a man

38:57.916 --> 38:59.449
who killed an innocent kid.

38:59.451 --> 39:01.051
And he would've killed more,

39:01.053 --> 39:03.220
if we hadn't have stopped him.

39:03.222 --> 39:05.789
You don't see it, do you?

39:05.791 --> 39:08.291
That I'm soft? Yeah, I see it clearly.

39:08.293 --> 39:10.827
You're not.

39:10.829 --> 39:14.064
He was lonely and you connected to him,

39:14.066 --> 39:16.833
to the humanity in that moment.

39:19.705 --> 39:22.072
Feeling alone?

39:22.074 --> 39:23.507
It's a horrible thing.

39:23.509 --> 39:26.843
You're not alone.

39:26.845 --> 39:31.248
You have people who love you.

39:31.250 --> 39:33.884
I miss him.

39:33.886 --> 39:37.521
I miss him so much.

39:37.523 --> 39:38.855
Me too.

39:43.195 --> 39:45.595
So what are the chances
that I would run into you

39:45.597 --> 39:49.966
just days before my 2-year
bureau sabbatical runs out?

39:51.870 --> 39:53.470
It sounds like fate to me.

39:53.472 --> 39:55.372
[Laughs] Yeah?

39:59.144 --> 40:01.178
You know, there are no
hoops to jump through,

40:01.180 --> 40:03.046
if you wanna come back right now.

40:04.616 --> 40:07.451
[Melancholy tune continues]

40:13.025 --> 40:16.426
♪

40:22.701 --> 40:24.868
♪

40:29.241 --> 40:32.442
♪

40:39.218 --> 40:42.452
♪

40:50.395 --> 40:53.497
♪

40:53.499 --> 40:55.432
Life's too long to be alone.

40:59.037 --> 41:00.437
Let's go home.

41:00.439 --> 41:01.605
Yeah.

